'''双层爱尔兰夹荷兰三明治'''（{{lang-en|Double Irish with Dutch sandwich}}）是自1980年代后期以来，大多数[[美国|美国]][[跨国公司|跨国公司]]使用的一種[[避稅|避稅手法]]{{Efn|The ''Double Irish'' is sometimes misunderstood as being only used for EU–sourced revenues and business. For example, in 2016, Facebook recorded global revenues of $27 billion, while Facebook in Ireland paid €30 million in Irish tax on Irish revenues of €13 billion (approximately half of all global revenues).<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.ie/business/technology/facebook-paid-just-30m-tax-in-ireland-despite-earning-12bn-36362527.html |title=Facebook paid just €30m tax in Ireland despite earning €12bn |newspaper=[[Irish_Independent|Irish Independent]] |author=Adrian Weckler |date=29 November 2017 |access-date=23 April 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180421030708/https://www.independent.ie/business/technology/facebook-paid-just-30m-tax-in-ireland-despite-earning-12bn-36362527.html |archive-date=2018-04-21 |dead-url=no }}</ref> Similarly, when the EU introduced the [[GDPR|GDPR]] regulations in 2018, Facebook disclosed that all of its non-U.S. accounts (circa 1.9 billion, of which 1.5 billion were non-E.U), were legally based in Dublin.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-facebook-privacy-eu-exclusive/exclusive-facebook-to-put-1-5-billion-users-out-of-reach-of-new-eu-privacy-law-idUSKBN1HQ00P |title=Exclusive: Facebook to put 1.5 billion users out of reach of new EU privacy law |work=[[Reuters|Reuters]] |author=David Ingram |date=18 April 2018 |access-date=23 April 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180423112422/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-facebook-privacy-eu-exclusive/exclusive-facebook-to-put-1-5-billion-users-out-of-reach-of-new-eu-privacy-law-idUSKBN1HQ00P |archive-date=2018-04-23 |dead-url=no }}</ref> Similarly, Google is also believed to run most of its non–U.S. sales revenue and profits through its Dublin operation.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/business/2016/nov/04/google-pays-47m-euros-tax-ireland-22bn-euros-revenue |title=Google pays €47m in tax in Ireland on €22bn sales revenue |newspaper=[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]] |author=Simon Bowers |date=4 November 2016 |access-date=23 April 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180405153557/https://www.theguardian.com/business/2016/nov/04/google-pays-47m-euros-tax-ireland-22bn-euros-revenue |archive-date=2018-04-05 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.finfacts.ie/irishfinancenews/article_1026612.shtml|title=Google booked 41% of global revenues in Ireland in 2012; A leprechaun's gold?|publisher=Finfacts.ie|date=30 September 2013|access-date=6 November 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171213171339/http://www.finfacts.ie/irishfinancenews/article_1026612.shtml|archive-date=2017-12-13|dead-url=no}}</ref>|name="mistake"}}。該手法由[[蘋果公司|苹果公司]]首創。截止2010年，美国跨国公司每年通過双层爱尔兰夹荷兰三明治這一手法避稅1000亿美元{{Efn|Before the US 2017 TCJA repatriation tax, the Double Irish shielded all non–US profits of US multinationals from: (a) taxation in the end-consumer market, (b) from taxation in Ireland, and (c) from US taxation. The 2017 TCJA placed a 15.5% US tax on these untaxed profits, and they were deemed to be automatically repatriated (regardless of whether the US multinational wanted to repatriate the untaxed profits or not).}}。

根據[[爱尔兰|愛爾蘭]]政策，如果一家公司總部在愛爾蘭以外，实际营运也在愛爾蘭以外，則該公司在愛爾蘭的分公司享有零税率优惠，且向公司總部匯款也無需支付稅款。實際在愛爾蘭運營的則需要上繳12.5％企业所得税率。另外根據[[荷兰|荷蘭]]稅收政策，[[歐盟|歐盟]]境內的公司交易，無須支付[[所得稅|企業所得稅]]，只需支付低廉的[[交易稅|交易稅]]<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|title=苹果避税740亿美元，三明治手法大公开|url=http://finance.people.com.cn/n/2013/0624/c348883-21947525.html|accessdate=|author=人民網|date=|format=|publisher=|language=|archive-date=2018-08-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180822104029/http://finance.people.com.cn/n/2013/0624/c348883-21947525.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite web|title=苹果公司的避税“三明治”是怎么做的|url=http://m.opinion.caixin.com/zknews/2017-01-24/101048451.html?utm_source=Zaker&utm_medium=ZakerAPP&utm_campaign=Hezuo|accessdate=|author=财新网|date=|format=|publisher=|language=}}</ref><ref name=":2">{{Cite web|title=一张图看懂苹果与硅谷“兄弟们”的避税套路，天才们的创造力你不会懂|url=https://36kr.com/p/1721173327873|accessdate=|author=36氪|date=|format=|publisher=|language=}}</ref><ref name=":3">{{Cite web|title=看谷歌是如何成为“避税大户”的？ 仅2016年就省下37亿美元|url=http://www.nbd.com.cn/articles/2018-01-03/1178912.html|accessdate=|author=每日經濟新聞|date=|format=|publisher=|language=|archive-date=2018-10-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181005012510/http://www.nbd.com.cn/articles/2018-01-03/1178912.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=":4">{{Cite web|title=全球究竟有多少资产被隐藏在海外？|url=https://www.bbc.com/zhongwen/simp/business-40772540|accessdate=|author=BBC|date=|format=|publisher=|language=|archive-date=2018-06-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180609024159/http://www.bbc.com/zhongwen/simp/business-40772540|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

一般美國跨國公司會採用以下措施避稅，首先在愛爾蘭設立實際運營的公司A，將美國以外的收入歸入A，作為A的營業收入。同時還在愛爾蘭設立公司B、荷蘭設立公司C。而B的公司總部所在地為[[加勒比海|加勒比海]]某個[[避稅天堂|避稅天堂]]。公司將所有產品的[[知识产权|知識產權]]劃歸為B公司所有，B再授權給C，C再授權給A。而A一旦有營業收入，必須將收入作為[[版稅|版稅]]支付給C，同時A支付的版稅作為公司運營成本還能抵扣一定的稅收，C再向B支付版稅。B再將收入匯入公司總部賬戶。如果B直接向A授權，B會被認為實際運營在愛爾蘭境內，因而美國跨國公司會選擇在荷蘭開設公司C。設在愛爾蘭的企業A和B就像[[三明治|三明治]]的兩片麵包，荷蘭企業C就像三明治中的夾層食物，因而這一避稅手法得名双层爱尔兰夹荷兰三明治<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1" /><ref name=":2" /><ref name=":3" /><ref name=":4" />。

通過三家公司的運作，美國跨國公司的海外收入税率仅为约2～3％，而如果將海外收入汇回美国，則至少要支付35％的联邦企业税率<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1" /><ref name=":2" /><ref name=":3" /><ref name=":4" />。

由於避稅太多，在外部壓力下，2020年1月，[[蘋果公司|蘋果公司]]、[[Google|Google]]、[[Facebook|Facebook]]等美國跨國公司逐步放棄這一避稅手法{{efn|It is believed that Ireland's extreme economic exposure to US corporate BEPS activity, had led Ireland to expand into more traditional [[tax_haven|tax haven]]–type tools, such as the ''[[Qualifying_investor_alternative_investment_fund_(QIAIF)|Qualifying investor alternative investment fund (QIAIF)]]'' (designed to compete with the Cayman Islands SPC), and the ''[[Irish_Section_110_Special_Purpose_Vehicle_(SPV)|Irish Section 110 Special Purpose Vehicle (SPV)]]'' (designed to compete with the Luxembourg SPV).<ref name="ftt">{{cite news |title=Ireland enjoys tax boom but fears a reckoning: Dublin concerned about reliance on revenue from small group of multinational companies |url=https://www.ft.com/content/c69ed976-fbab-11e7-9b32-d7d59aace167 |newspaper=[[Financial_Times|Financial Times]] |author=Arthur Beesley |date=31 January 2018 |access-date=26 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180705180005/https://www.ft.com/content/c69ed976-fbab-11e7-9b32-d7d59aace167 |archive-date=2018-07-05 |dead-url=no }}</ref>|name="taxhaven"}}。各國政府計劃設置[[全球最低企業稅率|全球最低企業稅率]]以減少跨國公司避稅問題。

